  "prompt": "What are the best colleges for an MBA in the world other than IIM's?",
  "response": "There are many top colleges around the world known for their MBA programs besides the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs). Here\u2019s a list of some of the best MBA colleges globally:\n\n1. **Harvard Business School** (USA)\n2. **Stanford Graduate School of Business** (USA)\n3. **University of Pennsylvania (Wharton)** (USA)\n4. **MIT Sloan School of Management** (USA)\n5. **Columbia Business School** (USA)\n6. **London Business School** (UK)\n7. **INSEAD** (France/Singapore)\n8. **Chicago Booth School of Business** (USA)\n9. **Northwestern University (Kellogg)** (USA)\n10. **University of California\u2014Berkeley (Haas)** (USA)\n11. **HEC Paris** (France)\n12. **University of Cambridge (Judge Business School)** (UK)\n13. **University of Oxford (Sa\u00efd Business School)** (UK)\n14. **University of Michigan\u2014Ann Arbor (Ross)** (USA)\n15. **University of Virginia (Darden)** (USA)\n\nThese institutions are renowned for their academic excellence, strong alumni networks, and high employability rates for graduates. When choosing an MBA program, consider factors such as curriculum, faculty, specializations, location, culture, and career services.",
